KW  - Going-concern audit report
KW  - Lottery-type stocks
KW  - Retail investors
KW  - Market underreaction
AB  - We explain why the market underreacts to the certified extreme financial distress signal conveyed by the auditor's going-concern (GC) opinion. We conjecture that GC stocks attract retail investors with gambling proclivities. Splitting our GC sample into lottery-like and non-lottery-like firms, we find that the anomaly is concentrated in lottery-like firms, which underperform by −17 % to −32 % over the following year. A range of analyses confirm retail investors with greater propensity to gamble are more likely to trade lottery-like GC stocks. We conclude that retail investor gambling-motivated trading behavior is a key driver of the going-concern market paradox.
ER  - 
